HEADWORD: Postea
<hw>Post"e*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., after these
or those (things), afterward.]</ety> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>The return of
the judge before whom a cause was tried, after a verdict, of what was
done in the cause, which is indorsed on the <xex>nisi prius</xex>
record.</def> <rj><au>Wharton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Postel</ent>⟦br⟧
